        <releasenotes>
            <![CDATA[
            <h3>Version 2.0.63 - Fix False 100% Completion</h3>

            <h4>Bug Fixes</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Fixes SCORM showing 1/1 (100% complete) before total slides are detected</li>
                <li>totalSlides sent as 0 (unknown) until real total is detected, preventing false 100%</li>
                <li>Generic detection now sends a progress update when total slides changes</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Changes</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>totalSlides=0 in postMessage when slidescount &lt;= 1 (signals unknown total to SmartLearning)</li>
                <li>When generic detection updates slidescount (e.g. from 1 to 5), immediately sends corrected progress</li>
                <li>Flow: initial 1/0 (unknown) → generic detects TOTAL_SLIDES=5 → updates to 1/5 (20%)</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Previous Versions</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>v2.0.62: DOM-based total slides, suppress false 100%, fix initial dip</li>
                <li>v2.0.61: Generic SCORM 0-indexed fix, JS variable total detection</li>
            </ul>
            ]]>
        </releasenotes>
